### Plagued Proto-Dragons
During the Scourge’s spread across Northrend, a cult of worship had begun among native vrykul populations, recently awoken from long slumber. Worshipping the Lich King as a god of death, the vrykul of the Storm Peaks began volunteering to the cause their longtime, ancient animal companions - the proto-dragons, their long-established pets, mounts and friends.

So incensed by this, the necromancers and plague-doctors of the Scourge resumed long abandoned experiments in crafting a new breed of dragon, a plagued dragonflight crafted to spread disease wherever they may fly. In the past this had failed miserably, with few living past whelphood.

Through the use of blighted pools loaded with countless clutches of stolen eggs, the throwback dragon species were far more receptive than the old experiments, and were able to grow into adulthood despite their infusion with deathly, sickly disease. Bleached a pale green and with eternally addled minds, these great, loyal beasts were broken from birth to obey their necromancer masters, and were granted as gifts to vrykul champions of the Scourge, to act as mounts and as vectors of further infection.

The new dragonflight of plagued proto-dragons took to the sky, a terrifying reminder of the totality of the Lich King’s reign over Northrend, reducing even its ancient heritage to his minions.

### Plagued Dragons

Beneath the earth in the dread catacombs of Scholomance, the Cult of the Damned performed sick and twisted experiments on the living. Even dragons were not exempt, as the Cult had "procured" some Black Dragonflight eggs, and had begun efforts to create a living dragonflight worthy of the Scourge.

Sickly green in hue and diseased from the egg, constantly covered in sores and festering wounds, these insane creatures know only suffering and pain, which they seek only to inflict upon others. Through their blighted breath they flood their foes with sickness, spreading the dreaded Plague of Undeath to the living.

***Infant mortality.*** As the Cult has learned, deathly disease causes the rapid end of life, and as such most of these foul creatures have died before they could reach adulthood. Those that do not may also become so unstable or sick that they are simply unable to function. Indeed, a great portion of the experiments - and why the Cult constantly needs new eggs - have been devoted to working out how to extend the dragonwhelps' lives, and suffering, further. 

***Affront to life.*** No people of morality or goodwill may sleep soundly knowing these creatures are alive and suffering, and some groups have devoted their time to eliminating this experiment for good. Unfortunately, they realise that the only way to end the experiment is to end Scholomance itself, a task sought out only by the most powerful among Azeroth's defenders. 

