> ## Plagued Dragon <!-- https://wc5e-cr-calculator.frogvall.com/?3;17;200;12;20;104;44;43;44;43;44;0;0;0;0;0;0;;;;1;2;;;;;;;1;;1;3;;;;;;;;10;;;;;1;;4;;;15;Death%20and%20Decay -->
> *Huge undead (dragon), lawful evil*
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 17 (natural armor)
> - **Hit Points** 200 (16d12 + 96)
> - **Speed** 40 ft., fly 80 ft.
>___
> |  STR  |  DEX  |  CON  |  INT  |  WIS  |  CHA  |
> |:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|
> |23 (+6)|10 (+0)|22 (+6)| 8 (-1)|15 (+2)|18 (+4)|
>___
> - **Saving Throws** Dex +6, Con +12
> - **Skills**  Perception +8, Survival +8
> - **Damage Immunities** poison, necrotic
> - **Condition Immunities** poisoned
> - **Senses** blindsight 10 ft., darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 18
> - **Languages** Common, Draconic
> - **Challenge** 17 (18,000 XP)
> ___
>
> ***Deadly Plague.*** Poison damage that the dragon deals ignores resistance and immunity to poison damage. It can inflict the poisoned condition even on creatures normally immune to it. When it deals a critical hit, the target is infected with the plague of undeath.
>
> ***Legendary Resistance (3/Day).*** If the dragon fails a saving throw, it can choose to succeed instead.
>
> ***Plague Cloud.*** Any creature that starts its turn within 30 feet of the dragon must succeed on a DC 20
Constitution saving throw or take 9 (2d8) poison damage and be poisoned until the start of the creature's next turn. 
>
> ***Plagued Blood.*** When the dragon takes damage of any type but psychic, each creature within 15 feet of the dragon takes 9 (2d8) poison damage.
>
> ### Actions
> ***Multiattack.*** The dragon can use its Cannibalize. It then makes two attacks: one with its bite and one with its claws.
>
> ***Bite.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +12 to hit, reach 10 ft., one target. *Hit:* 17 (2d10 + 6) piercing damage plus 13 (3d8) poison damage.
>
> ***Claw.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +12 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. *Hit:* 13 (2d6 + 6) slashing damage.
>
> ***Tail Sweep.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +12 to hit, <br/> reach 15 ft., all targets in reach. *Hit:* 15 (2d8 + 6) bludgeoning damage.
>
> ***Cannibalize.*** The dragon cannibalizes the corpse of a dragon or humanoid within 10 feet that has been dead for less than a day, regaining 26 (4d12) hit points. Each creature of the dragon's choice that is within 60 feet of the dragon and can see it must succeed on a DC 18 Wisdom saving throw or become frightened for 1 minute. A creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success. If a creature's save is successful or the effect ends for it, the creature is immune to any dragon's cannibalize for the next 24 hours.
>
> <br/><br/>
> 
> ***Breath Weapons (Recharge 5-6).*** The drake uses one of the following breath weapons.
>
> **Dreadful Breath.** The drake exhales sludge in a 60-foot 
<br/>    cone. Each creature in that area must make a DC 20 
<br/>    Dexterity saving throw, taking 52 (15d6) poison 
<br/>    damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on 
<br/>    a successful one. A creature that fails their saving 
<br/>    throw by 5 or more must make a DC 15 Constitution 
<br/>    save or contract the plague of undeath.
<br/> In addition, any humanoid killed by the dreadful breath 
<br/>    rises at the start of the dragon's turn as a zombie 
<br/>    that is permanently under its command, following its 
<br/>    verbal orders to the best of its ability.
> <br/> **Shadow Breath.** The drake exhales shadowy fire in a 
<br/>    60-foot cone. Each creature in that area must 
<br/>    make a DC 20 Strength saving throw or take 
<br/>    17 (5d6) necrotic damage at the start of each of its 
<br/>    turns and have disadvantage on Strength-based 
<br/>    attack rolls, checks, and saving throws for 1 minute. 
<br/>    A creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of 
<br/>    each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a 
<br/>    success.
>
> ***Change Shape.*** The dragon can magically polymorph into a humanoid or back into its true form. Its humanoid form always appears to be sickly and half-rotted. It reverts to its true form if it dies. Any equipment it is wearing or carrying is absorbed or borne by the new form (its choice). 
> <br/>    In a new form, the dragon retains its alignment, hit points, ability to speak, proficiencies, Legendary Resistance, and Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma scores, as well as this action.
>
>
> ### Legendary Actions
> The dragon can take 3 legendary actions, choosing from the options below. Only one legendary action option can be used at a time and only at the end of another creature's turn. The dragon regains spent legendary actions at the start of its turn.
>
> **Call Darkness.** In a 30-foot radius of the dragon, bright 
<br/>    light becomes dim light and dim light becomes 
<br/>    darkness. Any nonmagical light sources within the 
<br/>    area have the light they produce suppressed. This 
<br/>    effect lasts until the end of the dragon's next turn 
<br/>    and moves with the dragon.
> <br/> **Wrack.** Target creature within 120 feet the dragon can 
<br/>    see must succeed on a DC 18 Wisdom saving throw 
<br/>    or have disadvantage on Strength-based attack rolls, 
<br/>    checks, and saving throws for 1 minute. A creature 
<br/>    can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its 
<br/>    turns, ending the effects on itself on a success.
> <br/> **Death and Decay (Costs 2 Actions).** Each non-undead 
<br/>    creature within 30 feet must make a DC 18
<br/>    Constituion saving throw, taking 13 (3d8) necrotic 
<br/>    damage on a failed save. Until the end of its next 
<br/>    turn, whenever the creature makes an attack roll 
<br/>    or saving throw, it must roll a d4 and subtract the 
<br/>    number rolled from the attack roll or saving throw. 
<br/>    A successful save results in half damage and no
<br/>    other effects.
> <br/> **Wing Attack (Costs 2 Actions).** The dragon beats its 
<br/>    wings. Each creature within 10 feet of the dragon 
<br/>    must succeed on a DC 20 Dexterity saving throw or 
<br/>    take 13 (2d6 + 6) bludgeoning damage and be 
<br/>    knocked prone. The dragon can then fly up to half its 
<br/>    flying speed.

